
[1]treacherously

   TREACHEROUSLY, adv. trech'erously. By violating allegiance or faith
   pledged; by betraying a trust; faithlessly; perfidiously; as, to
   surrender a fort to an enemy treacherously; to disclose a secret
   treacherously.

   You treacherously practic'd to undo me.
